Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 11:38:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?[DOSKUTSU]=20dos:=20Phase=209=20wave=2016.3=20p?=
 =?UTF-8?q?atch=200030=20=E2=80=94=20LFB-force=20env=20override?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The wave 16.2 banked-flush real-HW capture (2026-04-29) showed the
bottom ~35 scanlines (= 11,264 bytes / 320 bytes-per-line) rendering
black on the g2k Cirrus banked path even with patch 0029's bank-1
offset rewrite. Sentinel match=1 within a single flush, but the
audit-readback line `DOSVESA-FB-VRAM-BANK1 00 00 00 00 ...` proves
bank-1 data does not persist between flushes on this Cirrus.

Modeset log shows `has_lfb=1 use_lfb=0 banked=1 lfb_addr=0x78000000`
— the BIOS DOES expose an LFB on this Cirrus, but our SDL/0019
auto-disable forces banked because of the OEM-string fingerprint
match. SDL/0019 was authored against the cirrus5 wave-5 capture
where LFB was decoupled from the displayed VRAM region; the wave
16.3 hypothesis is that this particular Cirrus chip / BIOS does
have a working LFB, and that engaging it retires the entire
banked-mode bug class AND gains bandwidth (LFB is direct memcpy,
no banked overhead).

This patch adds an experimental escape hatch:
SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB=1 overrides both the SDL/0019 Cirrus
auto-detect AND the SDL_HINT_DOS_DISABLE_LFB manual disable, forcing
LFB at both the mode-set layer (SDL_dosmodes.c:838 force_banked
calculation, fed to VBE 0x4F02 SETMODE_LFB at line ~855) AND the
FB-state-populate layer (SDL_dosframebuffer.c:367 force_banked
calculation, fed to use_lfb_path at line ~370). Both layers stay
in sync per patch 0020's policy.

The hint is strict-match per CLAUDE.md DOSKUTSU env-var convention
(`e && e[0] == '1' && e[1] == 0`) so SET FORCE_LFB=0 / empty / unset
all leave SDL/0019's auto-disable behaviour intact. Default behaviour
is unchanged; the override only fires when the iter explicitly opts in.
The env-var name SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB matches the symbol
constant identically (same convention as SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_BANK_SENTINEL,
SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_PUMP_YIELD).

One diagnostic line lands in SDLDBG.LOG at modeset time:

    WAVE16-3-LFB-FORCE: hint=<unset|set> use_lfb=<0|1>
    lfb_addr=0x%08lx fb_size=%lu

so each iter capture has one grep'able token confirming which path
was taken. Routes through DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG → doskutsu_dbg_log →
SDLDBG.LOG (or <TAG>SDL.LOG when DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG is set, per patch
0024).

Why DOS needs this
------------------

Wave 16.1 sentinel confirmed that the banked-flush mechanism does
work within a single flush iteration on this Cirrus, but data does
not persist between flushes — pointing at either a Cirrus-specific
banked-window auto-shadow that VBE doesn't expose, or a BIOS-side
bank-pointer reset on each VBE call. We've spent two iters trying
to fix banked at the VRAM-write layer; the next experiment is
sidestepping banked entirely. If LFB works, retire the banked path
on this card. If LFB fails the same way it did on cirrus5, leave
the auto-disable in place and chase the banked persistence bug at
the VBE 0x4F05 SetWindow level next iter.

This patch only adds the override; the existing diagnostic patches
(0027 audit, 0028 sentinel, 0029 offset rewrite) remain in place
as passive observers so the iter capture can correlate banked-side
behaviour against LFB-side behaviour when the hint flips.

Local-only patch per workspace policy. Never PR'd upstream.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
